title: JIP Abdul Majeed wins PB-16 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Jamat-e-Islami Pakistan (JIP) candidate Abdul Majeed has won the Balochistan Assembly election from PB-16, Jaffarabad by securing 15,248 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Pakistan Muslim League Nawaz (PML-N) Rahat Jamali who bagged 14,131 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn out remained 36.28 per cent.
